Revised 2020-2021 School Year Calendar First Day of School - August 10, 2020
June 16, 2020
Due to the likelihood of on-going COVID-19 health and safety concerns, and the potential for school disruption, TEA has recommended that school districts adjust their school calendars to maximize instructional time for the upcoming school year. To help meet this need, Kemp ISD has made revisions to the
2020-2021 school calendar. These changes were approved by the Kemp ISD school board, Monday, June 15. [Please be advised, further changes to the calendar may be needed as events related to COVID-19 arise.]
Here are the board approved revisions to the 20-21 school year calendar:
• School will begin on August 10th rather than August 17th.
• Fall Break in September has been changed to two (2) days instead of five
(5) days.
• Christmas break will begin December 18, an Early Releases Day
• School will resume on January 4, 2021, for teachers and January 5, 2021, for students
• The last day of school will be May 25th, this is unchanged.

It is National Library Week. While the physical libraries are closed, all librarians have been working diligently to provide access to digital reading materials and to curate resources for learning at home.

Celebrate by sharing what you love about the virtual services available at your library. Post to Instagram, Twitter, or on the I Love Libraries Facebook page, about an e-book, audiobook, virtual storytime or book club, or how your library has made a difference while you've been social distancing at home. Use the hashtag #ThankYouLibraries and tag your library.

Dear KISD Parents,
With our recent announcement of school closure due to the coronavirus through Friday, April 3rd, I want to share our plans to continue providing breakfast and lunch to "any" student 18 years of age or younger.

Beginning, Wednesday, March 25th from 10:30 AM-11:30 AM, both bagged breakfast and lunch will be available for curbside pick-up. Those meals will remain available through the school closure date of Friday, April 3rd.

Two designated campuses will be the two locations in the district to pick up all meals. Those two campus locations are: KEMP PRIMARY SCHOOL and KEMP JUNIOR HIGH SCHOOL. Either location is an option for your family to choose from.

Please note the first week of meal service will be WEDNESDAY-FRIDAY. (March 25, March 26, March 27) The second week of meal service will be MONDAY-FRIDAY.(March 30, March 31, April 1st, April 2nd, April 3rd)

For additional support or needs regarding meals, please contact Ms. Raye Kennedy Smith at raye.kennedy@kempisd.org.

Please stay safe and stay well.

Thank you,
Dr. Lisa A. Gonzales
Superintendent of Schools

If you should have questions, please call our campus offices of your child for further information.

Busses will run at 1:00 PM and Mr. Neel is apprising his drivers of this notification to assure students riding buses are accommodated.

Thank you KISD Parents for your support with this safety decision.

Dr. Lisa A. Gonzales
Superintendent

post_text:
Golf teams advanced to Regionals - On Tuesday, April 2nd, the Yellowjacket, and Lady Jacket golf teams competed in the District 18-3A tournament at Cedar Creek Country Club.

The Yellowjackets secured back-to-back district titles with a 33 stroke victory over runner-up, Malakoff. Boomer Irvin placed 2nd overall with a score of 99, and Ethyn Irvin took 3rd overall with a 104. Dylan Ashcraft, Cameron Clamon, Mason Claver, and Taylor Donovan solidified the title and a trip to the Regional Tournament at Brenham Country Club on April 22nd-23rd.

Also advancing to the regional tournament, the Lady Jackets finished Runner-up. Reece Tanksley, Gabby Sherrill, Anna Christie, Jaylynn Hefti, and Aleah Pruitt will compete at Brenham Country Club on April 24th-25th.

Congratulations to these student-athletes who manage to play other sports and working jobs while finding time to practice golf and represent their school and community with class. Good luck at Region! http://edl.io/n1021821

post_text:
Major Milestone for Kemp ISD athletics.

The long-awaited Kemp High School Weight room facility hit a major milestone this past week. Contractors were on site early Thursday morning to pour the foundation. The new 8400 sq. ft. facility will include a 4,800 sq. ft. weight room area as well as new showers and locker rooms for the boys Varsity and JV teams. Completion of the steel structure should follow quickly in the coming weeks.

Discussions on future plans for our Athletic program include the expansion and renovation of the existing girl’s locker room, remodel of the concession stand and restroom facility upgrades at the athletic fields.

Exciting times for our district as we strive to continue to improve our facilities for the future of all our students.

Completion of the steel structure should follow quickly in the coming weeks.

Discussions on future plans for our Athletic program include the expansion and renovation of the existing girl’s locker room, remodel of the concession stand and restroom facility upgrades at the athletic fields.

post_text: Bryce Francis and Kane Johnson both qualified for the State Track Meet this past weekend, at the Regional meet! They will be competing in Austin on May 11th & 12th. Bryce won the discus competition, and Kane placed 2nd in the 110 High Hurdles at the Regional competition which qualified them both for their events for the State Meet in Austin. This is a phenomenal accomplishment and these guys represented our school well! Good luck to you both! http://edl.io/n710968

The Girls Powerlifting Team recently competed in the Regional meet in Fairfield. They walked away with the 3rd Place Team Trophy, 3 State Qualifiers, 1 Outstanding Lifter, and 2 Regional record holders.
Those who qualified for the State Meet in Waco March 16th - 17th are Andrea Beasley~Regional Record, Bethany Alexander, Alicia Dennis~Outstanding Lifter & Regional Record.
The Team and their weight classes are, Andrea Beasley~259+, Bethany Alexander~148, Alicia Dennis~123, Delanie Spakes~259, Jaylin Contreras~123, and Carmen Villarreal~114.
The team is Coached by JJ Williams, Steve Stewart and Macy Gilcrease.

post_text:
Flu Letter from Superintendent - Kemp ISD is monitoring student and staff absences related to illness. Over the last day we have seen an increase in students and staff with cold and flu-like symptoms. We have students with confirmed cases of the flu that are resting at home today. We have taken several steps to address this issue, including working with our custodial staff to disinfect all areas. Another step we are considering at this time is cancelling classes for Thursday, December 21st, if cases of cold and flu continue to increase. We will make this decision on Wednesday morning, December 20th, and communicate it before 10:00 a.m. Please monitor our Facebook pages and our website for updates.

I have asked campus administrators to reschedule campus Christmas activities for Wednesday afternoon.

Kemp ISD is also monitoring school time needed for the school year, and at this time will not need to make up any missed days. http://edl.io/n800132

post_text: Kemp ISD will dismiss school on Sept. 1st at 2:00 p.m. - This is due to an athletic event that evening which is being held in Rio Vista, a 2 hour bus trip. Kemp ISD will run regular bus routes earlier to provide the safest environment for our students. This will allow Kemp ISD to still have enough buses back in the district to safely transport our kids to the game in a timely manner. With the challenge of having to drive kids on that date through rush hour traffic in Dallas to reach Rio Vista, the early release time is needed. http://edl.io/n739653

sf "The Book of Everything" Public Performance - On Friday, April 28th, at 7:00 p.m. in the KHS auditorium, the KHS OAP Theatre Group will be presenting scenes from "The Book of Everything" for public viewing. This is the award winning performance that earned our Kemp High School OAP the 3 A State Championship Trophy.
Tickets for all attendees will be $5 and you may obtain yours from Cynthia Bray at KHS (9034989225) or Angie Ellis at KISD Admin (9034981312) starting tomorrow, April 21st. We encourage you to buy your tickets early in preparation for a sell out crowd.

Funds from this performance will be used to send students to theatre camp this summer. http://edl.io/n701139
